---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About"
	description="The official blog of MavsBoard.com — Dallas Mavericks fan community since 2020."
	pubDate={new Date('April 11 2026')}
>
	<p>
		<strong>MavsBoard Blog</strong> is the official blog of <a href="https://www.mavsboard.com">MavsBoard.com</a>,
		the #1 Dallas Mavericks fan forum. We take the best discussions, hottest takes, and deepest analysis
		from our community and turn them into blog posts that are easy to read, share, and discover.
	</p>

	<h2>What We Cover</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Weekly Digests</strong> — The top forum discussions, curated and summarized</li>
		<li><strong>Game Recaps</strong> — Fan reactions and community analysis after Mavs games</li>
		<li><strong>Trade Rumors</strong> — What the community thinks about the latest rumors and deals</li>
		<li><strong>Player Spotlights</strong> — Deep dives on Mavs players from a fan perspective</li>
		<li><strong>Draft & Offseason</strong> — Prospect analysis, free agency takes, and roster moves</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Why This Blog Exists</h2>
	<p>
		MavsBoard's forum is packed with incredible fan insight — detailed game breakdowns, salary cap analysis,
		scouting reports, and passionate debate. But forum threads can be hard to discover through search engines,
		and not everyone has time to read through hundreds of posts.
	</p>
	<p>
		This blog bridges that gap. We use AI to help curate and summarize the best community content,
		then publish it here where it's easy to find, read, and share. Every post links back to the
		original forum thread so you can jump into the full discussion.
	</p>

	<h2>Join the Community</h2>
	<p>
		The blog is just the surface. The real action happens on <a href="https://www.mavsboard.com">MavsBoard Forum</a>.
		Join thousands of Mavs fans discussing every game, every trade, every draft pick. See you there.
	</p>

	<p><strong>Go Mavs!</strong></p>
</Layout>
